WEBVTT

NOTE Skit starts at anchor #4 in the civil service committee room.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.000
<v Politician>
Gentlemen, our MP saw the PM this AM and the PM wants more LSD from the PIB by tomorrow AM or PM at the latest... Now, the fiscal deficit... adjusted for seasonal variations...

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:18.000
<v First Official>
I think he's talking about taxation.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.000
<v Politician>
Bravo, Madge. Well done. Taxation is indeed the very nub of my gist. We have to find something new to tax.

00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:23.500
<v Second Official>
I understood that.

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:27.000
<v Third Official>
If I might put my head on the chopping block so you can kick it around a bit, sir...

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:28.500
<v Politician>
Yes?

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:33.000
<v Third Official>
Well most things we do for pleasure nowadays are taxed, except one.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:34.500
<v Politician>
What do you mean?

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:38.000
<v Third Official>
Well, er, smoking's been taxed, drinking's been taxed but not ... thingy.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.500
<v Politician>
Good Lord, you're not suggesting we should tax... thingy?

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:41.500
<v First Official>
Poo poo's?

00:00:41.500 --> 00:00:42.500
<v Third Official>
No.

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:46.000
<v First Official>
Thank God for that. Excuse me for a moment.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:47.500
<v Third Official>
No, no, no - thingy.

00:00:47.500 --> 00:00:49.000
<v Second Official>
Number ones?

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:50.500
<v Third Official>
No, thingy.

00:00:50.500 --> 00:00:51.500
<v Politician>
Thingy!

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:55.000
<v Second Official>
Ah, thingy. Well it'll certainly make chartered accountancy a much more interesting job.

